  <h1 class="gd-h1">Heliskiing vs Cat Skiing vs Ski Touring</h1>
  <p class="gd-lede">The short answer: pick <strong>heliskiing</strong> if you want the most vertical, the remotest terrain and a high-tempo day, and budget is not the deciding factor; pick <strong>cat skiing</strong> if you want a friendlier price and a day that keeps running when the cloud sits low; pick <strong>ski touring</strong> if you value self-reliance, quiet and the lowest cost, and you have the fitness and backcountry skills to earn each descent. If you cannot choose between the freedom of skinning and the reach of a helicopter, <a href="/heli-assisted-touring">heli-assisted touring</a> gives you both in one day. The rest of this guide compares the three honestly, so the right choice for <em>you</em> is obvious by the end.</p>
