      <details><summary>Which is cheapest: heliskiing, cat skiing or ski touring?</summary><p>Ski touring is by far the cheapest once you own the kit, because there is no lift or aircraft to pay for; a guided day is the main cost. Cat skiing sits in the middle, sharing the price of the snowcat and its operator across the group. Heliskiing is the most expensive, reflecting the helicopter, fuel, pilots and IFMGA guiding, but it also buys the most vertical per day.</p></details>
